cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it proposes a cache placement policy for wireless networks. It may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves designing a decentralized caching policy. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it discusses the promotion of item diversity and reciprocation among nodes. Finally, it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it compares the cache size requirements of different caching policies.
